    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This FD3S-generation chassis remains a masterclass in weight distribution and kinematics. Powered by the 13B-REW rotary engine, the sequential twin-turbocharger system executes a seamless transition between the primary and secondary turbines, providing a linear power band. The drivetrain features a precise five-speed manual transmission paired with a Torsen limited-slip differential for optimal power delivery out of corners. Significant attention has been paid to thermal management, including an upgraded aluminum radiator to prevent heat soak. The four-wheel double-wishbone suspension maintains factory geometry, ensuring the surgical steering response these cars are known for. While the aesthetics show minor signs of a life well-driven, the mechanical vitals\u2014including compression across all rotor faces\u2014are strong, making this a superb driver-spec example of Japanese performance engineering.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 9
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
